AKS Capacity Reservation Groups (CRG) – Financial Services Scenarios
Executive One-Pager
December 2025
Business Problem in Financial Services
Financial workloads (e.g., trading platforms, risk modeling, payment processing) demand instant, uninterrupted compute for compliance (e.g., PCI-DSS, SOX) and zero-tolerance SLAs. Azure capacity crunches—driven by surging AI/ML demand and supply-chain delays—can delay VM/AKS node provisioning by 15–90+ minutes, risking multimillion-dollar losses during peaks like market opens or quarter-ends. Official Azure Capacity Crunch Incidents:
2025 East US Shortfall (July): Multi-AZ VMSS issues for D/E-series SKUs; customers urged to migrate to AZ1/3 or East US 2. Microsoft Learn: Logical Zone Mapping
Ongoing 2025 Constraints: High demand blocks GPU/VM allocations in regions like North Central US; quota delays for ML endpoints. Q&A: Capacity Issues
Historical (2020–2024): COVID-era surges caused repeated allocation failures; Microsoft prioritized enterprises but new/pending users hit barriers. Azure Blog: Service Continuity
Troubleshooting Guide: AllocationFailed errors due to "unprecedented demand"; retry in alternate zones or use CRGs. Microsoft Learn: VM Allocation Failures
CRGs mitigate this by locking 100% guaranteed capacity for AKS manual node pools, ensuring no failures.
Short Summary of CRG
A Capacity Reservation Group (CRG) is an Azure resource that pre-reserves dedicated compute capacity (specific VM sizes and zones) for exclusive use by your VMs or AKS node pools. It guarantees 100% availability during high-demand periods, preventing allocation failures. Create via CLI/Portal/API within a group; attach to new manual AKS node pools using --crg-id. Ideal for finance's predictable peaks; billed hourly at pay-as-you-go rates (even unused), eligible for RI discounts.
Financial-Only Scenarios: 100% Guaranteed Compute with CRGs
CRGs shine in finance for predictable, high-stakes scaling. Target D/E/FX-series VMs for analytics/risk workloads. Combine with Reserved Instances for 72%+ savings.



