CRG vs. Reserved Instances (RI) – Quick Comparison
CRGs focus on availability guarantees, while RIs emphasize cost discounts. Use them together for optimal results in financial workloads.
Feature
Capacity Reservation Group (CRG)
Reserved Instances (RI)
Primary Focus
100% capacity guarantee (no allocation failures)
Up to 72% billing discount on committed usage
Availability Protection
Yes—locks capacity; fails creation if unavailable
No—prioritized access only, no hard guarantee
Cost Savings
None inherent (pay-as-you-go rates apply)
Deep discounts (1/3-year terms)
Commitment
Flexible—no term; create/delete anytime
Fixed 1-year or 3-year commitment
Billing
Hourly for reserved capacity (even if unused)
Discount applied only to running resources
Finance Use Case
Trading platforms needing instant failover
Steady-state risk modeling for long-term savings
Best Combo
CRG + RI = Guarantee + Discount (e.g., 72% off reserved capacity)
N/A


Cost of CRGs
CRGs are billed hourly at the same rate as the underlying VM size (pay-as-you-go pricing), whether the reserved capacity is used or unused—e.g., reserving 10 Standard_D2s_v3 VMs charges as if 10 VMs are running, even idle. No upfront commitment required, but you pay for the full reserved amount continuously. Discounts from Reserved Instances or Savings Plans apply automatically to both used and unused portions, potentially zeroing out costs for covered capacity.  


Bottom Line for Finance Execs
CRGs provide contractual 100% allocation reliability today—essential for zero-downtime trading and compliance in crunch-prone regions. Pair with RIs for up to 72% savings; deploy via manual AKS pools now, and simplify with native NAP integration in 2026 to future-proof your financial workloads.

@startuml
!theme plain
title AKS + CRG: Financial Workloads (Dec 2025)

package "Azure Subscription (East US)" {
  [Capacity Reservation Group\n(CRG)\nE/FX-series Reserved\n(for Finance SKUs)] as CRG

  package "AKS Cluster\n(NAP Enabled)" {
    node "Manual Node Pool\n(--crg-id)\nTrading/Risk Workloads" as ManualPool {
      rectangle "Pod\n(Order Execution,\nFraud ML)" as FinancePods
    }
    node "Auto-provisioned Pools\n(NAP)\nDev/Test Bursts" as NAPPools {
      rectangle "Pod\n(Reporting Sims)" as TestPods
    }
  }
}

CRG --> ManualPool : 100% Guaranteed\nNo Crunch Failures
ManualPool -down-> FinancePods : <10 min Scale
NAPPools -down-> TestPods : Best-Effort

